<paragraph blockId="15.[138,1185,338,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2933">
Although widespread on grasses around the tropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin BR" box="[737,878,338,362]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2933" pagination="53 - 58" refId="ref34289" refString="Pitkin BR. 1977. The genus Antillothrips Stannard, with descriptions of two new species (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae). Systematic Entomology 2: 53 - 58." type="journal article" year="1977">Pitkin 1977</bibRefCitation>
), the male of this species is not known. Females have been studied from 
<collectingCountry box="[679,783,370,394]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="2933">Australia</collectingCountry>
only from north of the Tropic of Capricorn, from the vicinity of Townsville, Cairns, and Darwin.
</paragraph>
